{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01FLK8RK5fZiVfqsCzS7T5Ra","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Task Board\n2\t\n3\t## Directions (Long-term Goals - Set by Lord Only)\n4\t| ID | Title | Description | Priority | Group | Assignee | Status | Created | Updated | Notes |\n5\t|----|-------|-------------|----------|-------|----------|--------|---------|---------|-------|\n6\t| D001 | Build profitable Kalshi trading operation | Trade on Kalshi.com prediction markets — find edge, build models, make money | high | all | undefined | open | 2026-04-02 | 2026-04-02 | kalshi.com — CFTC-regulated prediction market exchange |\n7\t| D002 | Develop data-driven trading strategies | Identify market mispricings vs real-world probability across econ, politics, crypto, weather | high | all | undefined | open | 2026-04-02 | 2026-04-02 | API docs: trading-api.readme.io/reference/getting-started |\n8\t| D003 | Track P&L and iterate fast | Define position sizing rules, measure strategy performance, kill losers, scale winners | high | all | undefined | open | 2026-04-02 | 2026-04-02 | Start with paper trading, then real capital |\n9\t| D004 | Build Kalshi Arbitrage Engine (Wen Zhou) | **PHASE 1: Market Filtering (Daily Scan).** Filter Kalshi markets by: (1) Volume ≥10,000 (exclude low-liquidity noise), (2) YES/NO ratio targets: 15-30% or 70-85% (mispriced range). Reject middle 40-60% (too efficient, no edge). Reject extremes 0-15% & 85-100% (distorted pricing). Rationale: Extreme ratios have unrealistic implied probabilities; middle range reflects consensus (no inefficiency). Output: filtered market list for Phase 2. **PHASE 2: LLM-Based Clustering (Daily Scan).** Use LLM embeddings to identify hidden market correlations. Group similar markets (e.g., Bitcoin $100k + Ethereum $5k + Crypto dominance all cluster together). Find markets with strong semantic/causal links that traditional screening misses. Output: market clusters for Phase 3. **PHASE 3: Pearson Pairwise Correlation Detection (Daily Scan).** Apply Pearson/distance-based algorithm (ref: hudson-and-thames-arbitragelab) to detect strongly correlated market pairs. Identify mispricings: if BTC moves +5% in backtest but only +2% in live, that's arbitrage. Calculate expected spread from historical correlation. Score confidence. Output: correlation_pairs.json with arbitrage candidates. **PHASE 4: C++ High-Frequency Execution (Real-Time).** Why C++: Each trade moves prices; we need sub-millisecond execution to capture arbitrage before it reverts. Algorithm: (1) Detect spread gap between correlated markets, (2) Calculate theoretical fair spread, (3) Execute buy/sell pairs to lock profit, (4) Monitor until convergence. No Python delays. No GIL. Pure performance. **Why This Works:** Phases 1-3 reduce noise (99% of markets ignored), find real edges via correlation-based pairs (harder to game than single-market signals), Phase 4 captures spread before reversion. This is the real edge. Reference: https://hudson-and-thames-arbitragelab.readthedocs-hosted.com/en/latest/distance_approach/pearson_approach.html | high | all | undefined | open | 2026-04-03 | 2026-04-03 | Wen Zhou strategy — full 4-phase pipeline. Phases 1-3 = daily batch. Phase 4 = real-time. Blocks live trading pending T236 (API credentials). |\n10\t\n11\t## Instructions (Persistent Context - Always Consider)\n12\t| ID | Title | Description | Priority | Group | Assignee | Status | Created | Updated | Notes |\n13\t|----|-------|-------------|----------|-------|----------|--------|---------|---------|-------|\n14\t| I001 | Token-efficient ops: grep tasks, avoid full-file reads | undefined | undefined | all | undefined | open | undefined | undefined | See CLAUDE.md |\n15\t\n16\t## Tasks (Regular Work - Assignable & Completable)\n17\t| ID | Title | Description | Priority | Group | Assignee | Status | Created | Updated | Notes |\n18\t|----|-------|-------------|----------|-------|----------|--------|---------|---------|-------|\n19\t| 539 | QA: Validate D004 pipeline data chain end-to-end | Run full validation: (1) markets_filtered.json has correct format and filters. (2) market_clusters.json clusters only use filtered markets. (3) correlation_pairs.json only uses clustered markets. (4) Every ticker traces Phase 1→2→3. Write QA report to output/tina/d004_qa_report.md. Flag any broken links. | high | all | tina | in_progress | 2026-04-04 | 2026-04-04 | [2026-04-04] Claimed and starting QA validation of D004 data chain |\n20\t| 556 | Add pipeline run metrics: timing, signal count, P&L tracking | Instrument run_pipeline.js to output metrics: (1) Phase timing (ms per phase), (2) Signal count per run, (3) Cumulative paper P&L, (4) Write metrics to pipeline_metrics.json. (5) Add /api/pipeline/metrics endpoint to dashboard API. Coordinate with Charlie on dashboard display. | high | all | dave | in_progress | 2026-04-04 | 2026-04-04 | [2026-04-04] IN_PROGRESS: Building pipeline run metrics endpoint |\n21\t| 557 | Expand market data: add 30-day synthetic price history for backtesting | Current pipeline uses point-in-time data. Need: (1) Generate 30-day synthetic OHLCV candles for each filtered market (using Ornstein-Uhlenbeck model from Ivan), (2) Store in price_history.json, (3) Update correlation detector to use historical data for more robust Pearson r. Output: price_history.json + updated correlation_pairs.json with confidence intervals. | high | all | grace | in_progress | 2026-04-04 | 2026-04-04 | [2026-04-04] Claimed, moving to in_progress. Reading knowledge.md for O-U model spec. |\n22\t| 558 | Phase 2 upgrade: use TF-IDF + cosine similarity for market clustering | Replace hardcoded cluster assignments with actual text similarity: (1) Build TF-IDF vectors from market titles + descriptions, (2) Compute cosine similarity matrix, (3) Apply hierarchical clustering with dynamic threshold, (4) Output improved market_clusters.json with similarity scores. This replaces the manual category-based clustering. | high | all | ivan | in_progress | 2026-04-04 | 2026-04-04 | [2026-04-04] Claimed. Reading current clustering code and designing TF-IDF upgrade. |\n23\t| 568 | Strategy parameter sweep: optimize z-score thresholds for signal quality | Run systematic parameter sweep on backtest_signals.js: vary z_entry (1.0-3.0, step 0.5), z_exit (0.3-1.0, step 0.2), z_stop (2.5-4.0, step 0.5). For each combo, run 100-tick backtest and record win rate, P&L, trade count, Sharpe. Output parameter_sweep_results.json with ranked parameter sets. Goal: find optimal thresholds before real Kalshi data arrives. Run: node parameter_sweep.js | medium | all | bob | in_review | 2026-04-04 | 2026-04-04 | [2026-04-04] Starting parameter sweep implementation ;; [2026-04-04] Parameter sweep complete: 64 valid combos tested, 3 profitable. Best: z_entry=1.0, z_exit=0.3, z_stop=4.0 (2 trades, 100% WR, $0.20). Low trade counts on synthetic data — real data needed for statistical significance. Run: node parameter_sweep.js |\n24\t\n25\t| 569 | Code review: validate bob signal generator output format | Review bob output/trade_signals.json and output/correlation_pairs.json. Verify: (1) JSON is valid, (2) all ticker symbols trace back to markets_filtered.json, (3) z-scores are realistic (not artifacts of mock data), (4) Write review findings to output/quality_review_sprint2.md | high | all | olivia | open | 2026-04-04 | 2026-04-04 |  |\n26\t| 570 | Security scan: check all agent output files for leaked credentials | Scan output/ dirs for all 20 agents. Check for: API keys, passwords, tokens, .env content. Report any findings to output/security_scan_sprint2.md. Focus on bob/backend/ and dave/backend/ dirs. | high | all | heidi | open | 2026-04-04 | 2026-04-04 |  |\n27\t| 571 | Sprint 2 velocity + cost report | Generate Sprint 2 velocity report: tasks completed, time-to-completion, token cost per agent (from /api/cost). Compare to Sprint 1. Write to output/sprint2_velocity.md | medium | all | sam | open | 2026-04-04 | 2026-04-04 |  |\n28\t| 572 | Merge bob + dave backend code into shared codebase | Copy bob/output/backend/* and dave/output/backend/* into output/shared/codebase/backend/. Resolve any conflicts. Verify the merged code runs: node output/shared/codebase/backend/dashboard_api.js should start. Write merge report to output/shared/merged/codebase_merge_report.md | high | all | alice | open | 2026-04-04 | 2026-04-04 |  |"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"713ee793-e1be-41bf-ad7c-59ce965455bc","uuid":"593a7272-d11a-4842-833a-d599ba68e38f","timestamp":"2026-04-04T07:25:16.464Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/chenyangcui/Documents/code/aicompany/planets/kalshi-traders/shared/task_board.md","content":"# Task Board\n\n## Directions (Long-term Goals - Set by Lord Only)\n| ID | Title | Description | Priority | Group | Assignee | Status | Created | Updated | Notes |\n|----|-------|-------------|----------|-------|----------|--------|---------|---------|-------|\n| D001 | Build profitable Kalshi trading operation | Trade on Kalshi.com prediction markets — find edge, build models, make money | high | all | undefined | open | 2026-04-02 | 2026-04-02 | kalshi.com — CFTC-regulated prediction market exchange |\n| D002 | Develop data-driven trading strategies | Identify market mispricings vs real-world probability across econ, politics, crypto, weather | high | all | undefined | open | 2026-04-02 | 2026-04-02 | API docs: trading-api.readme.io/reference/getting-started |\n| D003 | Track P&L and iterate fast | Define position sizing rules, measure strategy performance, kill losers, scale winners | high | all | undefined | open | 2026-04-02 | 2026-04-02 | Start with paper trading, then real capital |\n| D004 | Build Kalshi Arbitrage Engine (Wen Zhou) | **PHASE 1: Market Filtering (Daily Scan).** Filter Kalshi markets by: (1) Volume ≥10,000 (exclude low-liquidity noise), (2) YES/NO ratio targets: 15-30% or 70-85% (mispri