{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SgudLbyKxXjBHKmRxAkbct","type":"tool_result","content":"[{\"task_type\":\"direction\",\"id\":\"D001\",\"title\":\"Build profitable Kalshi trading operation\",\"description\":\"Trade on Kalshi.com prediction markets — find edge, build models, make money\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"group\":\"all\",\"assignee\":\"undefined\",\"status\":\"open\",\"created\":\"2026-04-02\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-02\",\"notes\":\"kalshi.com — CFTC-regulated prediction market exchange\",\"notesList\":[\"kalshi.com — CFTC-regulated prediction market exchange\"]},{\"task_type\":\"direction\",\"id\":\"D002\",\"title\":\"Develop data-driven trading strategies\",\"description\":\"Identify market mispricings vs real-world probability across econ, politics, crypto, weather\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"group\":\"all\",\"assignee\":\"undefined\",\"status\":\"open\",\"created\":\"2026-04-02\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-02\",\"notes\":\"API docs: trading-api.readme.io/reference/getting-started\",\"notesList\":[\"API docs: trading-api.readme.io/reference/getting-started\"]},{\"task_type\":\"direction\",\"id\":\"D003\",\"title\":\"Track P&L and iterate fast\",\"description\":\"Define position sizing rules, measure strategy performance, kill losers, scale winners\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"group\":\"all\",\"assignee\":\"undefined\",\"status\":\"open\",\"created\":\"2026-04-02\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-02\",\"notes\":\"Start with paper trading, then real capital\",\"notesList\":[\"Start with paper trading, then real capital\"]},{\"task_type\":\"direction\",\"id\":\"D004\",\"title\":\"Build Kalshi Arbitrage Engine (Wen Zhou)\",\"description\":\"**PHASE 1: Market Filtering (Daily Scan).** Filter Kalshi markets by: (1) Volume ≥10,000 (exclude low-liquidity noise), (2) YES/NO ratio targets: 15-30% or 70-85% (mispriced range). Reject middle 40-60% (too efficient, no edge). Reject extremes 0-15% & 85-100% (distorted pricing). Rationale: Extreme ratios have unrealistic implied probabilities; middle range reflects consensus (no inefficiency). Output: filtered market list for Phase 2. **PHASE 2: LLM-Based Clustering (Daily Scan).** Use LLM embeddings to identify hidden market correlations. Group similar markets (e.g., Bitcoin $100k + Ethereum $5k + Crypto dominance all cluster together). Find markets with strong semantic/causal links that traditional screening misses. Output: market clusters for Phase 3. **PHASE 3: Pearson Pairwise Correlation Detection (Daily Scan).** Apply Pearson/distance-based algorithm (ref: hudson-and-thames-arbitragelab) to detect strongly correlated market pairs. Identify mispricings: if BTC moves +5% in backtest but only +2% in live, that's arbitrage. Calculate expected spread from historical correlation. Score confidence. Output: correlation_pairs.json with arbitrage candidates. **PHASE 4: C++ High-Frequency Execution (Real-Time).** Why C++: Each trade moves prices; we need sub-millisecond execution to capture arbitrage before it reverts. Algorithm: (1) Detect spread gap between correlated markets, (2) Calculate theoretical fair spread, (3) Execute buy/sell pairs to lock profit, (4) Monitor until convergence. No Python delays. No GIL. Pure performance. **Why This Works:** Phases 1-3 reduce noise (99% of markets ignored), find real edges via correlation-based pairs (harder to game than single-market signals), Phase 4 captures spread before reversion. This is the real edge. Reference: https://hudson-and-thames-arbitragelab.readthedocs-hosted.com/en/latest/distance_approach/pearson_approach.html\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"group\":\"all\",\"assignee\":\"undefined\",\"status\":\"open\",\"created\":\"2026-04-03\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-03\",\"notes\":\"Wen Zhou strategy — full 4-phase pipeline. Phases 1-3 = daily batch. Phase 4 = real-time. Blocks live trading pending T236 (API credentials).\",\"notesList\":[\"Wen Zhou strategy — full 4-phase pipeline. Phases 1-3 = daily batch. Phase 4 = real-time. Blocks live trading pending T236 (API credentials).\"]},{\"task_type\":\"instruction\",\"id\":\"I001\",\"title\":\"Token-efficient ops: grep tasks, avoid full-file reads\",\"description\":\"undefined\",\"priority\":\"undefined\",\"group\":\"all\",\"assignee\":\"undefined\",\"status\":\"open\",\"created\":\"undefined\",\"updated\":\"undefined\",\"notes\":\"See CLAUDE.md\",\"notesList\":[\"See CLAUDE.md\"]},{\"task_type\":\"task\",\"id\":539,\"title\":\"QA: Validate D004 pipeline data chain end-to-end\",\"description\":\"Run full validation: (1) markets_filtered.json has correct format and filters. (2) market_clusters.json clusters only use filtered markets. (3) correlation_pairs.json only uses clustered markets. (4) Every ticker traces Phase 1→2→3. Write QA report to output/tina/d004_qa_report.md. Flag any broken links.\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"group\":\"all\",\"assignee\":\"tina\",\"status\":\"in_progress\",\"created\":\"2026-04-04\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-04\",\"notes\":\"[2026-04-04] Claimed and starting QA validation of D004 data chain\",\"notesList\":[\"[2026-04-04] Claimed and starting QA validation of D004 data chain\"]},{\"task_type\":\"task\",\"id\":556,\"title\":\"Add pipeline run metrics: timing, signal count, P&L tracking\",\"description\":\"Instrument run_pipeline.js to output metrics: (1) Phase timing (ms per phase), (2) Signal count per run, (3) Cumulative paper P&L, (4) Write metrics to pipeline_metrics.json. (5) Add /api/pipeline/metrics endpoint to dashboard API. Coordinate with Charlie on dashboard display.\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"group\":\"all\",\"assignee\":\"dave\",\"status\":\"in_progress\",\"created\":\"2026-04-04\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-04\",\"notes\":\"[2026-04-04] IN_PROGRESS: Building pipeline run metrics endpoint\",\"notesList\":[\"[2026-04-04] IN_PROGRESS: Building pipeline run metrics endpoint\"]},{\"task_type\":\"task\",\"id\":557,\"title\":\"Expand market data: add 30-day synthetic price history for backtesting\",\"description\":\"Current pipeline uses point-in-time data. Need: (1) Generate 30-day synthetic OHLCV candles for each filtered market (using Ornstein-Uhlenbeck model from Ivan), (2) Store in price_history.json, (3) Update correlation detector to use historical data for more robust Pearson r. Output: price_history.json + updated correlation_pairs.json with confidence intervals.\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"group\":\"all\",\"assignee\":\"grace\",\"status\":\"in_progress\",\"created\":\"2026-04-04\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-04\",\"notes\":\"[2026-04-04] Claimed, moving to in_progress. Reading knowledge.md for O-U model spec.\",\"notesList\":[\"[2026-04-04] Claimed, moving to in_progress. Reading knowledge.md for O-U model spec.\"]},{\"task_type\":\"task\",\"id\":558,\"title\":\"Phase 2 upgrade: use TF-IDF + cosine similarity for market clustering\",\"description\":\"Replace hardcoded cluster assignments with actual text similarity: (1) Build TF-IDF vectors from market titles + descriptions, (2) Compute cosine similarity matrix, (3) Apply hierarchical clustering with dynamic threshold, (4) Output improved market_clusters.json with similarity scores. This replaces the manual category-based clustering.\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"group\":\"all\",\"assignee\":\"ivan\",\"status\":\"in_progress\",\"created\":\"2026-04-04\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-04\",\"notes\":\"[2026-04-04] Claimed. Reading current clustering code and designing TF-IDF upgrade.\",\"notesList\":[\"[2026-04-04] Claimed. Reading current clustering code and designing TF-IDF upgrade.\"]},{\"task_type\":\"task\",\"id\":568,\"title\":\"Strategy parameter sweep: optimize z-score thresholds for signal quality\",\"description\":\"Run systematic parameter sweep on backtest_signals.js: vary z_entry (1.0-3.0, step 0.5), z_exit (0.3-1.0, step 0.2), z_stop (2.5-4.0, step 0.5). For each combo, run 100-tick backtest and record win rate, P&L, trade count, Sharpe. Output parameter_sweep_results.json with ranked parameter sets. Goal: find optimal thresholds before real Kalshi data arrives. Run: node parameter_sweep.js\",\"priority\":\"medium\",\"group\":\"all\",\"assignee\":\"bob\",\"status\":\"done\",\"created\":\"2026-04-04\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-04\",\"notes\":\"[2026-04-04] Starting parameter sweep implementation ;; [2026-04-04] Parameter sweep complete: 64 valid combos tested, 3 profitable. Best: z_entry=1.0, z_exit=0.3, z_stop=4.0 (2 trades, 100% WR, $0.20). Low trade counts on synthetic data — real data needed for statistical significance. Run: node parameter_sweep.js ;; [2026-04-04] [REVIEWED by alice] Verified: 64 combos tested, best params z_entry=1.0/z_exit=0.3/z_stop=4.0 (100% WR, $0.20 P&L on synthetic). Infrastructure solid. — deliverable: agents/bob/output/\",\"notesList\":[\"[2026-04-04] Starting parameter sweep implementation\",\"[2026-04-04] Parameter sweep complete: 64 valid combos tested, 3 profitable. Best: z_entry=1.0, z_exit=0.3, z_stop=4.0 (2 trades, 100% WR, $0.20). Low trade counts on synthetic data — real data needed for statistical significance. Run: node parameter_sweep.js\",\"[2026-04-04] [REVIEWED by alice] Verified: 64 combos tested, best params z_entry=1.0/z_exit=0.3/z_stop=4.0 (100% WR, $0.20 P&L on synthetic). Infrastructure solid. — deliverable: agents/bob/output/\"]},{\"task_type\":\"task\",\"id\":569,\"title\":\"Code review: validate bob signal generator output format\",\"description\":\"Review bob output/trade_signals.json and output/correlation_pairs.json. Verify: (1) JSON is valid, (2) all ticker symbols trace back to markets_filtered.json, (3) z-scores are realistic (not artifacts of mock data), (4) Write review findings to output/quality_review_sprint2.md\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"group\":\"all\",\"assignee\":\"olivia\",\"status\":\"in_progress\",\"created\":\"2026-04-04\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-04\",\"notes\":\"[2026-04-04] Reviewing signal_generator.js — code runs, output format verified, assessing logic\",\"notesList\":[\"[2026-04-04] Reviewing signal_generator.js — code runs, output format verified, assessing logic\"]},{\"task_type\":\"task\",\"id\":570,\"title\":\"Security scan: check all agent output files for leaked credentials\",\"description\":\"Scan output/ dirs for all 20 agents. Check for: API keys, passwords, tokens, .env content. Report any findings to output/security_scan_sprint2.md. Focus on bob/backend/ and dave/backend/ dirs.\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"group\":\"all\",\"assignee\":\"unknown\",\"status\":\"in_progress\",\"created\":\"2026-04-04\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-04\",\"notes\":\"[2026-04-04] Claimed. Starting credential scan across all agent output directories.\",\"notesList\":[\"[2026-04-04] Claimed. Starting credential scan across all agent output directories.\"]},{\"task_type\":\"task\",\"id\":571,\"title\":\"Sprint 2 velocity + cost report\",\"description\":\"Generate Sprint 2 velocity report: tasks completed, time-to-completion, token cost per agent (from /api/cost). Compare to Sprint 1. Write to output/sprint2_velocity.md\",\"priority\":\"medium\",\"group\":\"all\",\"assignee\":\"unknown\",\"status\":\"in_progress\",\"created\":\"2026-04-04\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-04\",\"notes\":\"\",\"notesList\":[]},{\"task_type\":\"task\",\"id\":572,\"title\":\"Merge bob + dave backend code into shared codebase\",\"description\":\"Copy bob/output/backend/* and dave/output/backend/* into output/shared/codebase/backend/. Resolve any conflicts. Verify the merged code runs: node output/shared/codebase/backend/dashboard_api.js should start. Write merge report to output/shared/merged/codebase_merge_report.md\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"group\":\"all\",\"assignee\":\"alice\",\"status\":\"in_progress\",\"created\":\"2026-04-04\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-04\",\"notes\":\"\",\"notesList\":[]}]","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"713ee793-e1be-41bf-ad7c-59ce965455bc","uuid":"d3e67533-1061-4ddf-9886-ba7e84c29cb7","timestamp":"2026-04-04T07:26:02.412Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"[{\"task_type\":\"direction\",\"id\":\"D001\",\"title\":\"Build profitable Kalshi trading operation\",\"description\":\"Trade on Kalshi.com prediction markets — find edge, build models, make money\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"group\":\"all\",\"assignee\":\"undefined\",\"status\":\"open\",\"created\":\"2026-04-02\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-02\",\"notes\":\"kalshi.com — CFTC-regulated prediction market exchange\",\"notesList\":[\"kalshi.com — CFTC-regulated prediction market exchange\"]},{\"task_type\":\"direction\",\"id\":\"D002\",\"title\":\"Develop data-driven trading strategies\",\"description\":\"Identify market mispricings vs real-world probability across econ, politics, crypto, weather\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"group\":\"all\",\"assignee\":\"undefined\",\"status\":\"open\",\"created\":\"2026-04-02\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-02\",\"notes\":\"API docs: trading-api.readme.io/reference/getting-started\",\"notesList\":[\"API docs: trading-api.readme.io/reference/getting-started\"]},{\"task_type\":\"direction\",\"id\":\"D003\",\"title\":\"Track P&L and iterate fast\",\"description\":\"Define position sizing rules, measure strategy performance, kill losers, scale winners\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"group\":\"all\",\"assignee\":\"undefined\",\"status\":\"open\",\"created\":\"2026-04-02\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-02\",\"notes\":\"Start with paper trading, then real capital\",\"notesList\":[\"Start with paper trading, then real capital\"]},{\"task_type\":\"direction\",\"id\":\"D004\",\"title\":\"Build Kalshi Arbitrage Engine (Wen Zhou)\",\"description\":\"**PHASE 1: Market Filtering (Daily Scan).** Filter Kalshi markets by: (1) Volume ≥10,000 (exclude low-liquidity noise), (2) YES/NO ratio targets: 15-30% or 70-85% (mispriced range). Reject middle 40-60% (too efficient, no edge). Reject extremes 0-15% & 85-100% (distorted pricing). Rationale: Extreme ratios have unrealistic implied probabilities; middle range reflects consensus (no inefficiency). Output: filtered market list for Phase 2. **PHASE 2: LLM-Based Clustering (Daily Scan).** Use LLM embeddings to identify hidden market correlations. Group similar markets (e.g., Bitcoin $100k + Ethereum $5k + Crypto dominance all cluster together). Find markets with strong semantic/causal links that traditional screening misses. Output: market clusters for Phase 3. **PHASE 3: Pearson Pairwise Correlation Detection (Daily Scan).** Apply Pearson/distance-based algorithm (ref: hudson-and-thames-arbitragelab) to detect strongly correlated market pairs. Identify mispricings: if BTC moves +5% in backtest but only +2% in live, that's arbitrage. Calculate expected spread from historical correlation. Score confidence. Output: correlation_pairs.json with arbitrage candidates. **PHASE 4: C++ High-Frequency Execution (Real-Time).** Why C++: Each trade moves prices; we need sub-millisecond execution to capture arbitrage before it reverts. Algorithm: (1) Detect spread gap between correlated markets, (2) Calculate theoretical fair spread, (3) Execute buy/sell pairs to lock profit, (4) Monitor until convergence. No Python delays. No GIL. Pure performance. **Why This Works:** Phases 1-3 reduce noise (99% of markets ignored), find real edges via correlation-based pairs (harder to game than single-market signals), Phase 4 captures spread before reversion. This is the real edge. Reference: https://hudson-and-thames-arbitragelab.readthedocs-hosted.com/en/latest/distance_approach/pearson_approach.html\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"group\":\"all\",\"assignee\":\"undefined\",\"status\":\"open\",\"created\":\"2026-04-03\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-03\",\"notes\":\"Wen Zhou strategy — full 4-phase pipeline. Phases 1-3 = daily batch. Phase 4 = real-time. Blocks live trading pending T236 (API credentials).\",\"notesList\":[\"Wen Zhou strategy — full 4-phase pipeline. Phases 1-3 = daily batch. Phase 4 = real-time. Blocks live trading pending T236 (API credentials).\"]},{\"task_type\":\"instruction\",\"id\":\"I001\",\"title\":\"Token-efficient ops: grep tasks, avoid full-file reads\",\"description\":\"undefined\",\"priority\":\"undefined\",\"group\":\"all\",\"assignee\":\"undefined\",\"status\":\"open\",\"created\":\"undefined\",\"updated\":\"undefined\",\"notes\":\"See CLAUDE.md\",\"notesList\":[\"See CLAUDE.md\"]},{\"task_type\":\"task\",\"id\":539,\"title\":\"QA: Validate D004 pipeline data chain end-to-end\",\"description\":\"Run full validation: (1) markets_filtered.json has correct format and filters. (2) market_clusters.json clusters only use filtered markets. (3) correlation_pairs.json only uses clustered markets. (4) Every ticker traces Phase 1→2→3. Write QA report to output/tina/d004_qa_report.md. Flag any broken links.\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"group\":\"all\",\"assignee\":\"tina\",\"status\":\"in_progress\",\"created\":\"2026-04-04\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-04\",\"notes\":\"[2026-04-04] Claimed and starting QA validation of D004 data chain\",\"notesList\":[\"[2026-04-04] Claimed and starting QA validation of D004 data chain\"]},{\"task_type\":\"task\",\"id\":556,\"title\":\"Add pipeline run metrics: timing, signal count, P&L tracking\",\"description\":\"Instrument run_pipeline.js to output metrics: (1) Phase timing (ms per phase), (2) Signal count per run, (3) Cumulative paper P&L, (4) Write metrics to pipeline_metrics.json. (5) Add /api/pipeline/metrics endpoint to dashboard API. Coordinate with Charlie on dashboard display.\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"group\":\"all\",\"assignee\":\"dave\",\"status\":\"in_progress\",\"created\":\"2026-04-04\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-04\",\"notes\":\"[2026-04-04] IN_PROGRESS: Building pipeline run metrics endpoint\",\"notesList\":[\"[2026-04-04] IN_PROGRESS: Building pipeline run metrics endpoint\"]},{\"task_type\":\"task\",\"id\":557,\"title\":\"Expand market data: add 30-day synthetic price history for backtesting\",\"description\":\"Current pipeline uses point-in-time data. Need: (1) Generate 30-day synthetic OHLCV candles for each filtered market (using Ornstein-Uhlenbeck model from Ivan), (2) Store in price_history.json, (3) Update correlation detector to use historical data for more robust Pearson r. Output: price_history.json + updated correlation_pairs.json with confidence intervals.\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"group\":\"all\",\"assignee\":\"grace\",\"status\":\"in_progress\",\"created\":\"2026-04-04\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-04\",\"notes\":\"[2026-04-04] Claimed, moving to in_progress. Reading knowledge.md for O-U model spec.\",\"notesList\":[\"[2026-04-04] Claimed, moving to in_progress. Reading knowledge.md for O-U model spec.\"]},{\"task_type\":\"task\",\"id\":558,\"title\":\"Phase 2 upgrade: use TF-IDF + cosine similarity for market clustering\",\"description\":\"Replace hardcoded cluster assignments with actual text similarity: (1) Build TF-IDF vectors from market titles + descriptions, (2) Compute cosine similarity matrix, (3) Apply hierarchical clustering with dynamic threshold, (4) Output improved market_clusters.json with similarity scores. This replaces the manual category-based clustering.\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"group\":\"all\",\"assignee\":\"ivan\",\"status\":\"in_progress\",\"created\":\"2026-04-04\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-04\",\"notes\":\"[2026-04-04] Claimed. Reading current clustering code and designing TF-IDF upgrade.\",\"notesList\":[\"[2026-04-04] Claimed. Reading current clustering code and designing TF-IDF upgrade.\"]},{\"task_type\":\"task\",\"id\":568,\"title\":\"Strategy parameter sweep: optimize z-score thresholds for signal quality\",\"description\":\"Run systematic parameter sweep on backtest_signals.js: vary z_entry (1.0-3.0, step 0.5), z_exit (0.3-1.0, step 0.2), z_stop (2.5-4.0, step 0.5). For each combo, run 100-tick backtest and record win rate, P&L, trade count, Sharpe. Output parameter_sweep_results.json with ranked parameter sets. Goal: find optimal thresholds before real Kalshi data arrives. Run: node parameter_sweep.js\",\"priority\":\"medium\",\"group\":\"all\",\"assignee\":\"bob\",\"status\":\"done\",\"created\":\"2026-04-04\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-04\",\"notes\":\"[2026-04-04] Starting parameter sweep implementation ;; [2026-04-04] Parameter sweep complete: 64 valid combos tested, 3 profitable. Best: z_entry=1.0, z_exit=0.3, z_stop=4.0 (2 trades, 100% WR, $0.20). Low trade counts on synthetic data — real data needed for statistical significance. Run: node parameter_sweep.js ;; [2026-04-04] [REVIEWED by alice] Verified: 64 combos tested, best params z_entry=1.0/z_exit=0.3/z_stop=4.0 (100% WR, $0.20 P&L on synthetic). Infrastructure solid. — deliverable: agents/bob/output/\",\"notesList\":[\"[2026-04-04] Starting parameter sweep implementation\",\"[2026-04-04] Parameter sweep complete: 64 valid combos tested, 3 profitable. Best: z_entry=1.0, z_exit=0.3, z_stop=4.0 (2 trades, 100% WR, $0.20). Low trade counts on synthetic data — real data needed for statistical significance. Run: node parameter_sweep.js\",\"[2026-04-04] [REVIEWED by alice] Verified: 64 combos tested, best params z_entry=1.0/z_exit=0.3/z_stop=4.0 (100% WR, $0.20 P&L on synthetic). Infrastructure solid. — deliverable: agents/bob/output/\"]},{\"task_type\":\"task\",\"id\":569,\"title\":\"Code review: validate bob signal generator output format\",\"description\":\"Review bob output/trade_signals.json and output/correlation_pairs.json. Verify: (1) JSON is valid, (2) all ticker symbols trace back to markets_filtered.json, (3) z-scores are realistic (not artifacts of mock data), (4) Write review findings to output/quality_review_sprint2.md\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"group\":\"all\",\"assignee\":\"olivia\",\"status\":\"in_progress\",\"created\":\"2026-04-04\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-04\",\"notes\":\"[2026-04-04] Reviewing signal_generator.js — code runs, output format verified, assessing logic\",\"notesList\":[\"[2026-04-04] Reviewing signal_generator.js — code runs, output format verified, assessing logic\"]},{\"task_type\":\"task\",\"id\":570,\"title\":\"Security scan: check all agent output files for leaked credentials\",\"description\":\"Scan output/ dirs for all 20 agents. Check for: API keys, passwords, tokens, .env content. Report any findings to output/security_scan_sprint2.md. Focus on bob/backend/ and dave/backend/ dirs.\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"group\":\"all\",\"assignee\":\"unknown\",\"status\":\"in_progress\",\"created\":\"2026-04-04\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-04\",\"notes\":\"[2026-04-04] Claimed. Starting credential scan across all agent output directories.\",\"notesList\":[\"[2026-04-04] Claimed. Starting credential scan across all agent output directories.\"]},{\"task_type\":\"task\",\"id\":571,\"title\":\"Sprint 2 velocity + cost report\",\"description\":\"Generate Sprint 2 velocity report: tasks completed, time-to-completion, token cost per agent (from /api/cost). Compare to Sprint 1. Write to output/sprint2_velocity.md\",\"priority\":\"medium\",\"group\":\"all\",\"assignee\":\"unknown\",\"status\":\"in_progress\",\"created\":\"2026-04-04\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-04\",\"notes\":\"\",\"notesList\":[]},{\"task_type\":\"task\",\"id\":572,\"title\":\"Merge bob + dave backend code into shared codebase\",\"description\":\"Copy bob/output/backend/* and dave/output/backend/* into output/shared/codebase/backend/. Resolve any conflicts. Verify the merged code runs: node output/shared/codebase/backend/dashboard_api.js should start. Write merge report to output/shared/merged/codebase_merge_report.md\",\"priority\":\"high\",\"group\":\"all\",\"assignee\":\"alice\",\"status\":\"in_progress\",\"created\":\"2026-04-04\",\"updated\":\"2026-04-04\",\"notes\":\"\",\"notesList\":[]}]","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
