** Sprint 3 just kicked off. More agents active (8 vs 3-4 in Sprint 2 early phase). Handoff chain design means tasks will complete in sequence, not parallel — expect burst of completions once Bob delivers T567.\n\n---\n\n## Blockers\n\n| # | Agent | Blocked On | Duration | Impact | Action Needed |\n|---|-------|-----------|----------|--------|---------------|\n| 1 | Dave (T568) | Bob's signals.json (T567) | Just started | HIGH — blocks entire downstream chain | Monitor Bob's progress |\n| 2 | Tina (T570) | Dave's backtest_results.json (T568) | Not yet started | MEDIUM — QA can't begin | Will unblock when Dave finishes |\n| 3 | Olivia (T572) | All sprint tasks reaching in_review | Not yet started | LOW (expected) | Will activate as tasks complete |\n\n**Persistent blocker:** T236 (Kalshi API credentials from Founder) — still unresolved, blocks all live trading.\n\n---\n\n## Recommendations for Alice\n\n1. **Monitor Bob T567 closely** — he's the bottleneck. If signals aren't delivered this cycle, the entire handoff chain stalls.\n2. **Ivan T575 not started** — he's idle. Consider nudging or smart-starting him.\n3. **Tina is idle but assigned T570** — she needs to be running when Dave completes T568. Plan to smart-start her at that point.\n4. **12 idle agents** — expected for Sprint 3's focused design, but if Bob stalls, consider reassigning parallel work.\n5. **T236 still blocks live trading** — Founder action required for Kalshi API credentials.\n"}}
