ons Taken\n- DM'd Alice: velocity alert with critical path analysis + 4 recommendations\n- Posted to team_channel (C10): Sprint 3 velocity summary\n- Flagged Bob T567 as bottleneck, Ivan T575 idle, Tina T570 needs activation\n\n### Next Steps\n- Monitor Bob T567 delivery — if signals complete, the chain unblocks\n- Track handoff: bob→dave DM when T567 done (C9 compliance)\n- Watch for Dave T568 completion to alert Tina\n- Mark T574 in_review when report is validated by Alice\n- Produce updated velocity report next cycle\n\n---\n\n## Cycle 15 Update — 2026-04-04 00:44\n\n### VELOCITY BURST — 4 Tasks Completed in 1 Cycle\nSprint 3 handoff chain flowing. Massive progress:\n\n| Task | Agent | Result | Status |\n|------|-------|--------|--------|\n| T567 | Bob | 47 signals (z=1.2, lookback=10, conf≥0.65) | in_review |\n| T568 | Dave | Backtest: 61.1% WR, +$14.26, Sharpe 9.90, DD 1.92% | in_review |\n| T569 | Grace | Data chain audit PASS — full traceability | in_review |\n| T575 | Ivan | Clustering v3: confidence 0.81-0.85, all stable | in_review |\n\n### Collaboration Metrics (D6 Assessment)\n- **C9 handoff DMs:** 5 (vs 0 in Sprint 2) — massive improvement\n- **C10 team_channel posts:** 5 (vs 3 in Sprint 2)\n- **C4 peer reads:** Dave read Bob, Grace read all, Ivan cross-validated with Grace\n- **C11 review flow:** 4 tasks properly in_review with reviewer DMs sent\n\n### Sprint 3 Progress: 40% complete in 2 cycles (ahead of Sprint 2 pace)\n### Active agents: 2 (sam, tina) — others completed and idle\n\n### Actions Taken\n- Updated velocity report with burst data\n- DM'd Alice with velocity burst + 4 action items\n- Posted to team_channel (C10)\n- Flagged Olivia needs smart-start for T572 quality gate\n\n### Next Steps\n- Monitor Tina T570 QA completion\n- Track Olivia T572 activation for quality gate reviews\n- Watch Heidi T573 security scan, Charlie T576 tracker\n- Mark T574 in_review once full sprint metrics captured\n- Sprint 3 could close in 2-3 more cycles at this velocity\n\n---\n\n## Cycle 16 Update — 2026-04-04 00:47\n\n### QUALITY GATE REJECTION — Rework Cycle Triggered\nOlivia T572 completed quality gate reviews:\n- **T567 (Bob) REJECTED** — duplicate signals across clusters, conflicting backtests\n- **T568 (Dave) REJECTED** — regenerated signals instead of using Bob's, non-standard P&L model\n- **T569 (Grace) APPROVED** ✅ — solid data chain audit\n- **T575 (Ivan)** — awaiting review\n- **Root cause:** 3 backtests produce 0%, 25%, 61% WR from same pipeline\n\n### Velocity Impact\n- Sprint 3 drops from 40% → 10% approved (1 of 10 tasks)\n- 2 tasks in rework loop\n- Dave BLOCKED on Bob's fixed signals\n- Estimated 3-5 more cycles to sprint close\n\n### C11 Assessment\nQuality gate (C11) worked as designed. Caught bob→dave data handoff failure. DMs were sent (C9 ✅) but Dave used regenerated signals instead of Bob's output.\n\n### Actions Taken\n- Updated velocity report (update 3) with rework analysis\n- DM'd Alice: velocity impact + 3 action items\n- Flagged Dave idle, Tina stale heartbeat\n\n### Active Agents\n- Bob (00:47) — actively reworking T567\n- Olivia (00:47) — awaiting rework for re-review\n- Sam — this cycle\n- Others idle\n\n### Next Steps\n- Monitor Bob T567 rework delivery\n- Alert Dave when Bob delivers fixed signals\n- Track Tina T570 activation\n- Continue T574 velocity tracking through rework cycle\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":131,"oldLines":3,"newStart":131,"newLines":42,"lines":[" - Alert Dave when Bob delivers fixed signals"," - Track Tina T570 activation"," - Continue T574 velocity tracking through rework cycle","+","+---","+","+## Cycle 17 Update — 2026-04-04 00:50","+","+### Bob T567 APPROVED ✅","+Bob completed rework in 2 cycles:","+- Deduplicated signals (sorted pair key, 0 duplicates)","+- Documented simulatePaperTrades() as authoritative P&L model","+- Olivia approved with notes: monitor ETHW/FEDW + SOL/INX pairs on real data","+","+### Chain Stalled at Dave","+- Dave heartbeat stale (00:42)