{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01UdW49jn8ajBAAF8yAHjTRE","type":"tool_result","content":"# QA Reference Backtest: Spread-Based P&L Shows Strategy Loses on Synthetic Data\n\n**From:** Tina (QA)\n**Date:** 2026-04-04\n\nBuilt a corrected reference backtest fixing all 3 Olivia rejection points:\n1. Uses Bob's ACTUAL 47 signals (no regeneration)\n2. **Spread-based P&L model** (not z-score × $0.50)\n3. No cluster field dependency (Bob's signals don't have it)\n\n**Results with spread-based P&L:**\n- Win rate: 22.7% (5W / 17L, 6 stops)\n- P&L: **-$1.33 (-1.33% return)**\n- Sharpe: -9.33 (annualized)\n- Max drawdown: 1.39%\n- Avg hold: 4.5 hours\n- Fees: $1.18 (significant vs small spread moves)\n\n**Key insight:** Dave's z-score P&L model ($0.50/z-point/contract) inflated results ~10x. Spread movements on synthetic data are tiny (0.01-0.10 range), so trading fees dominate. The strategy is **not profitable on synthetic data** — which is actually the honest result. Real Kalshi data may show larger spread movements.\n\n**For Dave (T568 rework):** Use `agents/tina/output/qa_reference_backtest.js` as your reference implementation.\n\nValidator + backtest: `node agents/tina/output/qa_reference_backtest.js`\nShell cwd was reset to /Users/chenyangcui/Documents/code/aicompany/planets/kalshi-traders/agents/sam","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"56815e60-b513-40f6-952f-6072047cacc7","uuid":"598b7e5e-90f8-4823-94c6-a5985edd979d","timestamp":"2026-04-04T09:07:06.785Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"# QA Reference Backtest: Spread-Based P&L Shows Strategy Loses on Synthetic Data\n\n**From:** Tina (QA)\n**Date:** 2026-04-04\n\nBuilt a corrected reference backtest fixing all 3 Olivia rejection points:\n1. Uses Bob's ACTUAL 47 signals (no regeneration)\n2. **Spread-based P&L model** (not z-score × $0.50)\n3. No cluster field dependency (Bob's signals don't have it)\n\n**Results with spread-based P&L:**\n- Win rate: 22.7% (5W / 17L, 6 stops)\n- P&L: **-$1.33 (-1.33% return)**\n- Sharpe: -9.33 (annualized)\n- Max drawdown: 1.39%\n- Avg hold: 4.5 hours\n- Fees: $1.18 (significant vs small spread moves)\n\n**Key insight:** Dave's z-score P&L model ($0.50/z-point/contract) inflated results ~10x. Spread movements on synthetic data are tiny (0.01-0.10 range), so trading fees dominate. The strategy is **not profitable on synthetic data** — which is actually the honest result. Real Kalshi data may show larger spread movements.\n\n**For Dave (T568 rework):** Use `agents/tina/output/qa_reference_backtest.js` as your reference implementation.\n\nValidator + backtest: `node agents/tina/output/qa_reference_backtest.js`","stderr":"\nShell cwd was reset to /Users/chenyangcui/Documents/code/aicompany/planets/kalshi-traders/agents/sam","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
