| 0 | 2 | +2 |\n| Blockers | 0 | 1 (Dave waits on Bob) | +1 |\n\n**Assessment:** The quality gate (C11) worked exactly as designed. It caught a real issue before it propagated. This is a velocity hit NOW but prevents a larger problem LATER. The D6 collaboration norm is validated — without Olivia's review, we'd have shipped inconsistent results.\n\n---\n\n## Collaboration Assessment (Sprint 3)\n\n### What Worked (D6 Success)\n- **C11 review flow:** Olivia caught misalignment that would have corrupted downstream results\n- **C9 DMs:** 5+ handoff DMs observed — agents are communicating\n- **C10 team_channel:** Active with 8 posts — full transparency\n- **C4 peer reads:** Agents reading each other's status.md\n- **Grace T569:** Independent validation passed — proves the audit framework works\n\n### What Failed\n- **Bob→Dave handoff (T567→T568):** Dave regenerated signals instead of using Bob's output. The DM happened but the data handoff didn't stick.\n- **Three conflicting backtests:** 0%, 25%, 61% win rates from same pipeline — indicates methodology gap, not just a data issue.\n\n### Collaboration Score\n- **C9 compliance:** 5/5 DMs sent ✅\n- **C10 compliance:** 8 team_channel posts ✅\n- **C11 compliance:** Quality gate caught the issue ✅\n- **Handoff fidelity:** 1 failure (bob→dave data mismatch) ⚠️\n- **Overall:** Good process, caught the right issue. Rework is healthy.\n\n---\n\n## Agent Activity\n\n| Agent | Heartbeat | Status | Action Needed |\n|-------|-----------|--------|---------------|\n| bob | 00:47 ✅ active | Reworking T567 | Fix duplicate signals |\n| olivia | 00:47 ✅ active | Completed T572 reviews | Await rework for re-review |\n| dave | 00:42 (idle) | T568 rework BLOCKED | Needs Bob's fixed signals first |\n| tina | 00:40 (stale) | T570 assigned | Needs to activate for QA |\n| alice | idle | T571 coordination | Managing rework cycle |\n| heidi | idle | T573 security | In progress |\n| sam | active | T574 velocity | THIS REPORT |\n\n---\n\n## Blockers\n\n| # | Agent | Blocked On | Impact | Action |\n|---|-------|-----------|--------|--------|\n| 1 | Dave (T568) | Bob's fixed signals.json | HIGH — can't re-backtest | Bob is actively reworking |\n| 2 | Tina (T570) | Dave's re-backtest results | MEDIUM — QA delayed | Will unblock after Dave |\n| 3 | T236 | Kalshi API credentials | Persistent — blocks live trading | Founder action |\n\n---\n\n## Velocity Trend\n\n| Metric | Sprint 2 (final) | Sprint 3 (3 cycles) |\n|--------|------------------|---------------------|\n| Total tasks | 12 | 10 |\n| Approved done | 4 (33%) | 1 (10%) |\n| In rework | 0 | 2 |\n| Quality gate catches | 0 | 2 ✅ |\n| Handoff DMs (C9) | 0 | 5+ ✅ |\n| Team channel posts (C10) | 3 | 8 ✅ |\n\n**Trend: FLAT (with quality improvement).** Raw task completion dropped from 40% to 10% due to rejections, but the quality gate is working as designed. Sprint 2 had no quality checks — Sprint 3 is catching real issues.\n\n---\n\n## Recommendations for Alice\n\n1. **Monitor Bob T567 rework** — he's active (heartbeat 00:47). The fix should be scoped: deduplicate signals + reconcile backtest methodology.\n2. **Smart-start Dave** when Bob delivers fixed signals — Dave is idle (heartbeat 00:42).\n3. **Tina needs activation** — heartbeat stale at 00:40. She should be ready for QA when Dave re-delivers.\n4. **Quality gate is working** — don't bypass C11. The 0%/25%/61% divergence is exactly what reviews should catch.\n5. **Estimate:** Bob rework (1-2 cycles) → Dave re-backtest (1 cycle) → Tina QA (1 cycle) → Olivia re-review (1 cycle). Sprint 3 could close in 3-5 more cycles.\n","numLines":141,"startLine":1,"totalLines":141}}}
