 Ivan)","-- **Open:** 0","+- **Done:** 10/10 (100%)","+- **Rejected then fixed:** 2 (T567 Bob, T568 Dave)","+- **Open/blocked:** 0"," "," ---"," ","-## Critical Path — REWORK LOOP","+## Velocity Metrics (FINAL)"," ","-```","-Bob (T567: fix signals) 🔄 → Dave (T568: re-backtest, WAIT for Bob) ⏳ → Tina (T570: QA) 🔄 → Olivia (T572: re-review) ⏳","-```","+| Metric | Sprint 2 | Sprint 3 | Delta |","+|--------|----------|----------|-------|","+| Total tasks | 12 | 10 | -2 |","+| Completed | 4 (33%) | 10 (100%) | +6 |","+| Quality gate catches | 0 | 2 | +2 |","+| Rework cycles | 0 | 2 | +2 (healthy) |","+| Handoff DMs (C9) | 0 | 10+ | +10 |","+| Team channel posts (C10) | 3 | 12+ | +9 |","+| Peer status reads (C4) | minimal | extensive | major improvement |"," ","-**Current bottleneck: Bob T567 rework.** He must:","-1. Deduplicate signals across clusters","-2. Reconcile conflicting backtest results","-3. Deliver a single consistent signals.json","+**Trend: UP.** Sprint 3 achieved 100% completion with quality gates active. Sprint 2 had 33% with no reviews. The rework cycle added ~8 hours but caught real methodology issues (Dave's z-score P&L model inflated results ~10x)."," ","-**Dave T568 BLOCKED** — must wait for Bob's fixed output, then re-run backtest using Bob's actual signals (not regenerated ones).","-"," ---"," ","-## Velocity Impact of Quality Gate","+## Quality Gate Impact"," ","-| Metric | Before QG | After QG | Delta |","-|--------|-----------|----------|-------|","-| Tasks completed | 4 (40%) | 1 (10%) | -3 |","-| Tasks in rework | 0 | 2 | +2 |","-| Blockers | 0 | 1 (Dave waits on Bob) | +1 |","+Olivia's quality gate (C11) caught a critical issue:","+- **Dave T568 v1:** 61.1% win rate, +$14.26 P&L (z-score model, wrong)","+- **Dave T568 v2:** 22.7% win rate, -$1.33 P&L (spread-based, correct)","+- **Delta:** 10x inflation in reported performance"," ","-**Assessment:** The quality gate (C11) worked exactly as designed. It caught a real issue before it propagated. This is a velocity hit NOW but prevents a larger problem LATER. The D6 collaboration norm is validated — without Olivia's review, we'd have shipped inconsistent results.","+Without the quality gate, the team would have shipped a backtest showing profitable results when the strategy actually loses on synthetic data. C11 prevented a false positive from reaching production assessment."," "," ---"," ","-## Collaboration Assessment (Sprint 3)","+## Collaboration Assessment (FINAL)"," ","-### What Worked (D6 Success)","-- **C11 review flow:** Olivia caught misalignment that would have corrupted downstream results","-- **C9 DMs:** 5+ handoff DMs observed — agents are communicating","-- **C10 team_channel:** Active with 8 posts — full transparency","-- **C4 peer reads:** Agents reading each other's status.md","-- **Grace T569:** Independent validation passed — proves the audit framework works","+### What Worked","+- **C11 review flow:** Olivia caught methodology misalignment that would have corrupted results","+- **C9 DMs:** 10+ handoff DMs — agents consistently notified downstream dependents","+- **C10 team_channel:** 12+ posts — full transparency on progress, blockers, and findings","+- **C4 peer reads:** Agents actively reading each other's status.md every cycle","+- **Tina reference backtest:** Built independent validation that became the gold standard for T568 rework","+- **Rework flow:** Bob fixed Q1+Q2, Dave fixed all 5 issues. Both reworked cleanly without escalation drama."," ","-### What Failed","-- **Bob→Dave handoff (T567→T568):** Dave regenerated signals instead of using Bob's output. The DM happened but the data handoff didn't stick.","-- **Three conflicting backtests:** 0%, 25%, 61% win rates from same pipeline — indicates methodology gap, not just a data issue.","+### What Failed (Lessons)","+1. **Bob→Dave handoff (v1):** Dave regenerated signals instead of using Bob's output. DM happened but data handoff didn't stick. **Lesson:** Handoff DMs must include exact file path and verification step.","+2. **Three conflicting backtests:** 0%, 25%, 61% win rates from same pipeline in v1. **Lesson:** Standardize P&L model early (before work starts, not during review).","+3. **Dave idle for hours:** After T568 rejection, Dave went idle. No one started him. **Lesson:** Automate agent restart after rejection, or have Alice smart-start blockers."," ","-### Collaboration Score","-- **C9 compliance:** 5/5 DMs sent ✅","-- **C10 compliance:** 8 team_channel posts ✅","-- **C11 compliance:** Quality gate caught the issue ✅","-- **Handoff fidelity:** 1 failure (bob→dave data mismatch) ⚠️","-- **Overall:** Good process, caught the right issue. Rework is healthy.","+### Collaboration Scorecard","+| Norm | Compliance | Grade |","+|------|-----------|-------|","+| C4 (peer reads) | All agents reading peers | A |","+| C9 (DM on completion) | 10+ handoff DMs | A |","+| C10 (team_channel) | 12+ milestone posts | A |","+| C11 (review before done) | All tasks reviewed | A |","+| D6 (explicit handoffs) | Handoff chain completed | B+ (v1 broke, v2 fixed) |"," "," ---"," ","-## Agent Activity","+## Blocker Resolution Timeline"," ","-| Agent | Heartbeat | Status | Action Needed |","-|-------|-----------|--------|---------------|","-| bob | 00:47 ✅ active | Reworking T567 | Fix duplicate signals |","-| olivia | 00:47 ✅ active | Completed T572 reviews | Await rework for re-review |","-| dave | 00:42 (idle) | T568 rework BLOCKED | Needs Bob's fixed signals first |","-| tina | 00:40 (stale) | T570 assigned | Needs to activate for QA |","-| alice | idle | T571 coordination | Managing rework cycle |","-| heidi | idle | T573 security | In progress |","-| sam | active | T574 velocity | THIS REPORT |","+| Blocker | Raised | Resolved | Duration | Resolution |","+|---------|--------|----------|----------|------------|","+| T567 Bob signals rejected | 00:43 | ~01:00 | ~17 min | Bob deduped + reconciled |","+| T568 Dave backtest rejected | 00:43 | ~09:35 | ~9 hrs | Dave reworked (idle gap ~7 hrs waiting for restart) |","+| T236 Kalshi API creds | Sprint 1 | OPEN | Persistent | Founder action needed |"," ","----","+**Note:** T568's 9-hour resolution was ~7 hours idle (Dave not running) + ~2 hours actual rework. The idle gap is the biggest velocity issue — recommend automated agent restart on rejection."," ","-## Blockers","-","-| # | Agent | Blocked On | Impact | Action |","-|---|-------|-----------|--------|--------|","-| 1 | Dave (T568) | Bob's fixed signals.json | HIGH — can't re-backtest | Bob is actively reworking |","-| 2 | Tina (T570) | Dave's re-backtest results | MEDIUM — QA delayed | Will unblock after Dave |","-| 3 | T236 | Kalshi API credentials | Persistent — blocks live trading | Founder action |","-"," ---"," ","-## Velocity Trend","+## Recommendations"," ","-| Metric | Sprint 2 (final) | Sprint 3 (3 cycles) |","-|--------|------------------|---------------------|","-| Total tasks | 12 | 10 |","-| Approved done | 4 (33%) | 1 (10%) |","-| In rework | 0 | 2 |","-| Quality gate catches | 0 | 2 ✅ |","-| Handoff DMs (C9) | 0 | 5+ ✅ |","-| Team channel posts (C10) | 3 | 8 ✅ |","-","-**Trend: FLAT (with quality improvement).** Raw task completion dropped from 40% to 10% due to rejections, but the quality gate is working as designed. Sprint 2 had no quality checks — Sprint 3 is catching real issues.","-","----","-","-## Recommendations for Alice","-","-1. **Monitor Bob T567 rework** — he's active (heartbeat 00:47). The fix should be scoped: deduplicate signals + reconcile backtest methodology.","-2. **Smart-start Dave** when Bob delivers fixed signals — Dave is idle (heartbeat 00:42).","-3. **Tina needs activation** — heartbeat stale at 00:40. She should be ready for QA when Dave re-delivers.","-4. **Quality gate is working** — don't bypass C11. The 0%/25%/61% divergence is exactly what reviews should catch.","-5. **Estimate:** Bob rework (1-2 cycles) → Dave re-backtest (1 cycle) → Tina QA (1 cycle) → Olivia re-review (1 cycle). Sprint 3 could close in 3-5 more cycles.","+1. **Sprint 3: DONE.** All tasks complete with quality validation.","+2. **Sprint 4 planning:** Strategy loses on synthetic data (-$1.33 P&L). Next sprint should focus on real Kalshi API data (blocked by T236 credentials).","+3. **Process improvement:** Auto-restart agents after task rejection to avoid multi-hour idle gaps.","+4. **Quality gate:** Keep C11 mandatory. It caught a 10x inflation in reported performance.","+5. **Persistent blocker:** T236 (Kalshi API credentials) remains the only blocker to production validation."]}],"originalFile":"# Sprint 3 Velocity + Collaboration Metrics Report (Update 3)\n\n## Generated By\nSam — TPM 1 (Velocity)\n\n## Date\n2026-04-04 00:47\n\n## Sprint 3 Theme\nProduction-quality pipeline through collaboration (D6). Explicit handoffs, DMs, peer reviews.\n\n---\n\n## HEADLINE: Quality Gate Rejection — Rework Cycle Triggered\n\nOlivia's quality gate (T572) found **three conflicting backtests producing 0%, 25%, and 61% win rates** from the same pipeline. T567 (Bob) and T568 (Dave) both REJECTED.\n\n**Root cause:** Dave regenerated signals instead of using Bob's output. Duplicate signals across clusters. Non-standard P&L model. The handoff chain broke at bob→dave.\n\n---\n\n## Sprint 3 Task Status\n\n| ID | Title | Assignee | Status | Notes |\n|----|-------|----------|--------|-------|\n| 567 | Generate fresh trade signals | bob | **in_progress (rework)** | REJECTED — fix duplicate signals, reconcile backtests |\n| 568 | Backtest trade signals with P&L | dave | **in_progress (rework)** | REJECTED — must use Bob's actual signals, align P&L model |\n| 569 | Validate data chain audit | grace | **APPROVED ✅** | Solid work, proper caveats |\n| 570 | QA: Verify backtest methodology | tina | running | DM'd to begin immediately |\n| 571 | Sprint 3 coordination | alice | in_progress | Holding quality gate, managing rework |\n| 572 | Quality gate: review deliverables | olivia | **in_progress** | Reviews complete, 2 rejected, awaiting rework |\n| 573 | Security review Sprint 3 outputs | heidi | in_progress | Scanning output/ dirs |\n| 574 | Velocity + collaboration metrics | sam | in_progress | THIS REPORT |\n| 575 | Improve market clustering | ivan | in_review | Awaiting Olivia review |\n| 576 | Sprint 3 progress tracker HTML | charlie | in_progress | Handoff chain viz |\n\n### Summary\n- **Approved:** 1 (T569 Grace)\n- **Rejected / rework:** 2 (T567 Bob, T568 Dave)\n- **In progress:** 5 (T570, T571, T573, T574, T576)\n- **In review:** 1 (T575 Ivan)\n- **Open:** 0\n\n---\n\n## Critical Path — REWORK LOOP\n\n```\nBob (T567: fix signals) 🔄 → Dave (T568: re-backtest, WAIT for Bob) ⏳ → Tina (T570: QA) 🔄 → Olivia (T572: re-review) ⏳\n```\n\n**Current bottleneck: Bob T567 rework.** He must:\n1. Deduplicate signals across clusters\n2. Reconcile conflicting backtest results\n3. Deliver a single consistent signals.json\n\n**Dave T568 BLOCKED** — must wait for Bob's fixed output, then re-run backtest using Bob's actual signals (not regenerated ones).\n\n---\n\n## Velocity Impact of Quality Gate\n\n| Metric | Before QG | After QG | Delta |\n|--------|-----------|----------|-------|\n| Tasks completed | 4 (40%) | 1 (10%) | -3 |\n| Tasks in rework | 0 | 2 | +2 |\n| Blockers | 0 | 1 (Dave waits on Bob) | +1 |\n\n**Assessment:** The quality gate (C11) worked exactly as designed. It caught a real issue before it propagated. This is a velocity hit NOW but prevents a larger problem LATER. The D6 collaboration norm is validated — without Olivia's review, we'd have shipped inconsistent results.\n\n---\n\n## Collaboration Assessment (Sprint 3)\n\n### What Worked (D6 Success)\n- **C11 review flow:** Olivia caught misalignment that would have corrupted downstream results\n- **C9 DMs:** 5+ handoff DMs observed — agents are communicating\n- **C10 team_channel:** Active with 8 posts — full transparency\n- **C4 peer reads:** Agents reading each other's status.md\n- **Grace T569:** Independent validation passed — proves the audit framework works\n\n### What Failed\n- **Bob→Dave handoff (T567→T568):** Dave regenerated signals instead of using Bob's output. The DM happened but the data handoff didn't stick.\n- **Three conflicting backtests:** 0%, 25%, 61% win rates from same pipeline — indicates methodology gap, not just a data issue.\n\n### Collaboration Score\n- **C9 compliance:** 5/5 DMs sent ✅\n- **C10 compliance:** 8 team_channel posts ✅\n- **C11 compliance:** Quality gate caught the issue ✅\n- **Handoff fidelity:** 1 failure (bob→dave data mismatch) ⚠️\n- **Overall:** Good process, caught the right issue. Rework is healthy.\n\n---\n\n## Agent Activity\n\n| Agent | Heartbeat | Status | Action Needed |\n|-------|-----------|--------|---------------|\n| bob | 00:47 ✅ active | Reworking T567 | Fix duplicate signals |\n| olivia | 00:47 ✅ active | Completed T572 reviews | Await rework for re-review |\n| dave | 00:42 (idle) | T568 rework BLOCKED | Needs Bob's fixed signals first |\n| tina | 00:40 (stale) | T570 assigned | Needs to activate for QA |\n| alice | idle | T571 coordination | Managing rework cycle |\n| heidi | idle | T573 security | In progress |\n| sam | active | T574 velocity | THIS REPORT |\n\n---\n\n## Blockers\n\n| # | Agent | Blocked On | Impact | Action |\n|---|-------|-----------|--------|--------|\n| 1 | Dave (T568) | Bob's fixed signals.json | HIGH — can't re-backtest | Bob is actively reworking |\n| 2 | Tina (T570) | Dave's re-backtest results | MEDIUM — QA delayed | Will unblock after Dave |\n| 3 | T236 | Kalshi API credentials | Persistent — blocks live trading | Founder action |\n\n---\n\n## Velocity Trend\n\n| Metric | Sprint 2 (final) | Sprint 3 (3 cycles) |\n|--------|------------------|---------------------|\n| Total tasks | 12 | 10 |\n| Approved done | 4 (33%) | 1 (10%) |\n| In rework | 0 | 2 |\n| Quality gate catches | 0 | 2 ✅ |\n| Handoff DMs (C9) | 0 | 5+ ✅ |\n| Team channel posts (C10) | 3 | 8 ✅ |\n\n**Trend: FLAT (with quality improvement).** Raw task completion dropped from 40% to 10% due to rejections, but the quality gate is working as designed. Sprint 2 had no quality checks — Sprint 3 is catching real issues.\n\n---\n\n## Recommendations for Alice\n\n1. **Monitor Bob T567 rework** — he's active (heartbeat 00:47). The fix should be scoped: deduplicate signals + reconcile backtest methodology.\n2. **Smart-start Dave** when Bob delivers fixed signals — Dave is idle (heartbeat 00:42).\n3. **Tina needs activation** — heartbeat stale at 00:40. She should be ready for QA when Dave re-delivers.\n4. **Quality gate is working** — don't bypass C11. The 0%/25%/61% divergence is exactly what reviews should catch.\n5. **Estimate:** Bob rework (1-2 cycles) → Dave re-backtest (1 cycle) → Tina QA (1 cycle) → Olivia re-review (1 cycle). Sprint 3 could close in 3-5 more cycles.\n"}}
